refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
resourcedbase_create stringpath arrayfields inttypeDBASE_TYPE_DBASE
dbase_create creates a dBase database with the given definition. If the file already exists, it is not truncated. dbase_pack can be called to force truncation.
&note.open-basedir.func;

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns a database resource if the database is successfully created,
 or &false; if an error occurred.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    dbase 7.0.0

     The type parameter has been added.




    dbase 7.0.0

     The return value is now a resource instead of an
     int.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Creating a dBase database file


<?php

// database "definition"
$def = array(
  array("date",     "D"),
  array("name",     "C",  50),
  array("age",      "N",   3, 0),
  array("email",    "C", 128),
  array("ismember", "L")
);

// creation
if (!dbase_create('/tmp/test.dbf', $def)) {
  echo "Error, can't create the database\n";
}

?>
